<http://www.spektrix.com/factorytheatre/event/143802ABPKKLLSRBMJKDBNPRSKKLSHQQK> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "Basbousa";
  schema:description """
	Young, Gifted, and Black is Obsidian Theatre’s arts training program dedicated to supporting Black theatre practitioners in non-performance disciplines. This four-month intensive explores Black diaspora theatre and performance aesthetics. YGB practitioners benefit from mentorship, masterclasses, and apprenticeships, with the program culminating in a collective-creation devised, directed, and designed by the YGB cohort.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>As the April 2023 conflict breaks out in Sudan, Adama in Toronto makes urgent phone calls to her grandmother Rania living in Khartoum. <span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Basbousa</span></span> is a story about the recipes we inherit, the homes we carry within us, and the impossible choices families make in times of crisis.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">25/26 Young, Gifted, and Black Cohort</span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Nála Simone Lendor</span> Costume Design<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Stephon Smith</span> Sound Design<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Ghislan Sutherland-Timm</span> Set Design<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Abigail Whitney</span> Directing<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"UnderlineText\">Basbousa Cast</span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Bola Aiyeola</span> Grandma Rania<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Megan Legesse</span> Adama<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Basbousa Creative Team<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Abigail Whitney</span> Director, Co-creator<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Ghislan Sutherland-Timm</span> Set Designer, Co-creator<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Nála Simone Lendor</span> Costume Designer, Co-creator<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Stephon Smith</span> Sound Designer, Co-creator<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Lilian Adom</span> Lighting Designer (YGB 24/25)<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Meryem Alaoui</span> Movement Consultant<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Mwahib Azreg</span> Cultural Consultant<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Robert Harding</span> Stage Manager<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">Aden Altamirano</span> Production Manager / Technical Director<span><br/></span><span class=\"BoldText\">ciaran brenneman</span> Head of Props<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Content Warnings:<span><br/></span><span class=\"ItalicText\"><span class=\"BoldText\">Basbousa</span></span> contains depictions and discussions of war, displacement, intergenerational trauma, pregnancy, family separation, and grief. The presentation includes references to armed conflict and humanitarian crisis, including sounds of gunfire, explosions, military sirens, shouting, and themes of death and loss.
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-05-29T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
