<http://www.spektrix.com/factorytheatre/event/143602AJLQKGTDTSMGJBRQVNKNMHJHLCJ> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "PUNCH: A New Musical";
  schema:description """
	From Andrew Seok, writer of 'Rosamund', 'Almost Ever After', 'The Man With The Golden Heart', comes the story of a monkey that captured hearts across the world after being bullied and carrying his beloved IKEA plush toy everywhere he went.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Abandoned at birth and raised by humans, Punch grows up between two worlds, never fully fitting into either. When released into a troop of 60 monkeys, he searches for where he belongs, and the courage to believe he is worthy of it.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Featuring:<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>BELINDA CORPUZ as Momo<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>CYRENA FIEL as Mama<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>CHILINA KENNEDY as The Narrator<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>LARA RODA as Punch<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>ANDREW SEOK as Akira<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>ALEX WIERZBICKI as Dad<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>HANEUL YI as The Zookeeper<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Written & Directed by: Andrew Seok<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Music Director / Piano: Scott Metcalf<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Presented by: Chaos & Light Productions and Eclipse Theatre Company<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Producers: Andrew Seok, M. Shane Aube<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Consulting Producer: Derrick Chua<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Poster Artwork & Design: Andrew Seok (Graphic Designer), Forrest Young (Sketch Artist), M.Shane Aube (Graphic Designer & Colourist), H.Mac (Line Artist)<span><br/></span><span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Duration: 90 minutes<span><br/></span>All ages
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-06-12T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
  schema:image <https://system.spektrix.com/factorytheatre/files/45c36756-2657-4796-8309-da37d707f57f.jpg>;
  schema:location <https://spektrix.com/factorytheatre/location/1AHGJDSMMPLMPPGNLJBQVLBRSKVDLQRPP>;
