<http://www.spektrix.com/factorytheatre/event/144202AMSTBJBBJMJNBRLRSJDSKLVDQMG> a
    schema:Event;
  schema:name "TEPS 2026 Showcase";
  schema:description """
	Factory Theatre’s Training Enhancement Programs is a workshop intensive for early career artists to collaborate, connect and create new work. Over the course of three weeks, our cohort of selected artists become members of a small theatre company where they participate in masterclasses, workshops, and readings, to stage a short performance work that is showcased at the end of the program. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>The training program is coordinated by Kalale Dalton-Lutale and has an acting, playwrighting and directing stream. Each of these streams supports artists in deepening their craft while expanding their experience creating new plays. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Our TEPs 2026 Cohort includes Abi Akinlade, Anna Morreale, Dipo Olawo, Ethan Keyes, Frosina Pejcinovska, jonnie lombard, Kendelle Parks, Lulu Liu, Naomi Morales, Olaoluwa Fayokun, Taelor Lewis Joseph & Taija Shonée Chung. <span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Our TEPs 2026 Facilitators include Claren Grosz, Gillian Clark & Khadijah Roberts-Abdullah
""";
  schema:startDate "2026-06-19T19:30:00"^^xsd:dateTime;
